# Plugin Testing

After every rebuild, test using the Roblox Studio MCP server. Never skip this loop.

## Prerequisites

This rule requires the Roblox Studio MCP server to be configured in Cursor.
If the MCP server is not available, fall back to manual testing:
ask the user to confirm the plugin works in Studio.

## Steps

1. Use the MCP server to open (or confirm open) the test place in Roblox Studio.
2. Trigger the plugin action via the toolbar button or UI panel.
3. Take a screenshot of the Studio viewport via the MCP server.
4. Analyze the screenshot — verify:
   - The plugin panel opens and closes correctly
   - The action runs without errors (check Output window)
   - The expected in-scene result is visible and correct
5. If any step fails, identify the issue, fix the code, rebuild, and re-test from scratch.
6. Only mark a change complete when the plugin behaves correctly end-to-end.
